Hey!
It's not working, one more time! Take that!
Ah, Wilbell! Are you practicing magic?

More or less. I don't want to cause another
forest fire like I did last time.

I could finally use magic at will,
I must work harder to train and cultivate myself!

Ha ha! You are very motivated!
... Hmm?

May I ask what's the stone
you are holding in your hand?

Ah, this? It's a magic accelerant.
You don't know about this thing?

Er... We use it in complicated magic occasionally.
Is this thing common in your world, Wilbell?

Yes, we use it to improve our magic power.
The effects are very different when you use accelerants.
Oh. We have a lot of differences though we are all witches.

Actually, I'm almost running out of
accelerants.

Hey, [px], you are an alchemist, right?
Can you make some for me?

No problem! Making items used in another world sounds
quite interesting huh? [px]!

Hee hee, thanks!
I appreciate that!

Hey, Wilbell!
What do you think?

Oh oh. Already done?
Thank you!

Wow, you are a real alchemist!
Accelerants made by alchemists are indeed of very good quality!
Is accelerant quality related to magic?

Of course! Alchemy can be used to increase purity
and extract even more powerful magic.

Hmm. Let's do this,
Wilbell, why don't you try practicing alchemy yourself?
That's great! Come synthesize with us!

Wow! It sounds suspicious!
Are you sure you are not discouraging me!?
Alchemy is too complicated for me... Nope!

Think about it! For a great witch like myself,
how could I do such a menial job, huh?
Hehe. I heard you say "complicated", didn't I?
You... heard me wrong! I didn't say that!

Great witches like me are very busy.
I better leave this thing to an expert!

[px], I'll come to you for help when my accelerants
have been used up. Thank you in advance!

OK... Now that I've got my accelerants,
I'm going to hone my skills. See you!

She was...
She was definitely trying to save her face, right?

Ha ha ha. After all, Wilbell
is still a child!
